<div dir="ltr">Howard,<div><br></div><div>I agree this is low priority, which is why I prefaced my report with &quot;I don&#39;t know if anybody cares&quot;.</div><div>I am happy to ignore this if it doesn&#39;t worry you.</div><div><br></div><div>In case you do want to proceed:</div><div><br></div><div>I configure on Carver with</div><div><font face="monospace, monospace" size="1">  --prefix=[...] --enable-debug CC=pgcc CXX=pgCC FC=pgf90 \</font></div><div><font face="monospace, monospace" size="1">  --with-tm=/usr/syscom/opt/torque/4.1.1 --enable-mpi-fortran=mpifh</font></div><div>(I know that &#39;tm&#39; path is out-of-date, but I&#39;ve never updated my build script.)</div><div><br></div><div>And I see common:libfabric and mtl:ofi enabled:</div><blockquote style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px"><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">{hargrove@cvrsvc04 LOG}$ grep -e :libfab -e :ofi configure.log </font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">--- MCA component common:libfabric (m4 configuration macro)</font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">checking for MCA component common:libfabric compile mode... dso</font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">checking if MCA component common:libfabric can compile... yes</font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">--- MCA component mtl:ofi (m4 configuration macro)</font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">checking for MCA component mtl:ofi compile mode... dso</font></div></div><div><div><font size="1" face="monospace, monospace">checking if MCA component mtl:ofi can compile... yes</font></div></div></blockquote><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>-Paul</div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Thu, Mar 5, 2015 at 8:57 AM, Howard Pritchard <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:hppritcha@gmail.com" target="_blank">hppritcha@gmail.com</a>&gt;</sp